    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1110"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1110">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/1210</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1595</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-19">May 19,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received May 23.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Supplementing despatch no. 1561, dated May 13,
                        1944,<note n="86" xml:id="d1110fn86">Not printed.</note> I have the honor to
                    report that Mr. Renwick<note n="87" xml:id="d1110fn87">William W. Renwick,
                        representative of the Fiscal Agent.</note> advised me today that the Fiscal
                    Agent under the Salvador loan contract has filed a protest with the Salvadoran
                    Government and with the Department of State<note n="88" xml:id="d1110fn88">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> against the proposed debt settlement
                    under negotiation between agents of the Salvadoran Government and the Foreign
                    Bondholders Protective Council Inc.</p>
                <p>Mr. Renwick added that he has submitted a memorandum to the Salvadoran
                    authorities on the subject (he stated he would give me a copy of the
                        memorandum),<note n="89" xml:id="d1110fn89">Copy transmitted to the
                        Department by the Ambassador in his despatch 1599, May 20, 1944; neither
                        printed.</note> suggesting that the proposed settlement be abandoned,
                    describing the settlement as an <hi rend="italic">ex-parte</hi> arrangement in
                    which the bondholders had no voice, and urging that as a provisional measure
                    service be resumed on the bonds on the basis of the Readjustment Agreement of
                    April 27, 1936.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walter Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
